s and the state sexual assault coalition, the West Virginia Foundation for Rape Information and Services, have dedicated nearly 45 years of crisis services and prevention efforts to support those impacted by sexual violence and to prevent future victimizations; therefore, be itResolved by the Senate: That the Senate hereby designates February 27, 2025, as Sexual Violence Awareness Day at the Legislature; and, be itFurther Resolved, That the Clerk is hereby directed to forward a copy of this resolution to the West Virginia Foundation for Rape and Information Services. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West Virginia Legislature's Office of Reference & Information.  | Terms of Use | Webmaster | © 2025 West Virginia Legislature ** Print On Demand Name: Email: Phone: